289
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:52,639
or whatever, you know that in a few hours,

290
00:16:52,639 --> 00:16:53,919
the sun will start coming up,

291
00:16:53,919 --> 00:16:57,399
and it's so beautiful that all your energy comes back.

292
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:12,960
He comes alive at night.

293
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:15,880
I think he's going to tear me apart. Let's go.

294
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:17,640
Let's go.

295
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:28,720
Oh my god.

296
00:17:29,519 --> 00:17:30,519
This trail...

297
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:33,920
It's indescribable.

298
00:17:36,839 --> 00:17:38,519
Hai Guai said it was indescribable.

299
00:17:38,799 --> 00:17:40,440
I think he was just too tired,

300
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,680
so tired that even the wind felt like a burden.

301
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:45,440
But when they saw the mountains

302
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:46,319
and the clouds,

303
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,920
their eyes lit up again.

304
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:52,359
People who spend time outdoors know that feeling:

305
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:54,039
your body is in hell,

306
00:17:54,279 --> 00:17:55,440
but your eyes are in heaven.

307
00:17:56,359 --> 00:17:57,359
And time

308
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,039
is always contradictory.

309
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:00,920
They want it to go faster

310
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,839
so they can get it over with,

311
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:05,039
but they also want it to slow down,

312
00:18:05,519 --> 00:18:08,319
because they don't want to fast-forward through the scenery.

313
00:18:37,279 --> 00:18:38,240
You really know how to pick a spot.

314
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:40,599
The prettiest internet-famous hut.

315
00:18:44,079 --> 00:18:46,440
On either side of every saddle,

316
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:48,119
the temperature

317
00:18:48,119 --> 00:18:49,319
can be completely different.

318
00:18:49,559 --> 00:18:51,279
So when you come out of the forest

319
00:18:51,279 --> 00:18:53,119
and see the meadow or the boulder field,

320
00:18:53,119 --> 00:18:55,720
your spirits lift,

321
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:57,640
and the fatigue eases a little.

322
00:18:57,640 --> 00:19:00,880
Every stretch around a summit is the essence of it.

323
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,640
I don't know. It's really hard to comprehend

324
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:19,920
before you've done a race like this.

325
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:22,559
It's basically one huge climb,

326
00:19:22,559 --> 00:19:24,119
because I slept in Donnas

327
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:28,559
and then left at around

328
00:19:28,559 --> 00:19:29,680
eleven-thirty or midnight.

329
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:34,559
There's basically a 2,400-meter climb.

330
00:19:36,519 --> 00:19:39,839
But one thing that surprised me was

331
00:19:39,839 --> 00:19:43,279
that even with all the ups and downs,

332
00:19:43,279 --> 00:19:44,319
in some ways

333
00:19:44,319 --> 00:19:47,240
you actually feel stronger as the race goes on.

334
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:49,240
It sounds strange to say that because obviously

335
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:51,480
I slowed down, and by the end

336
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:54,200
my quads were kind of injured, not really injured,

337
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:56,640
but overused and swollen.

338
00:19:58,119 --> 00:20:01,119
But even so, on the final climb,

339
00:20:01,119 --> 00:20:02,519
I felt strong,

340
00:20:02,519 --> 00:20:04,920
I felt stronger on the last hill

341
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:06,039
than I did on the first few.

342
00:20:06,039 --> 00:20:08,079
I felt like I'd adapted.

343
00:20:11,039 --> 00:20:15,240
The other thing I was thinking about a lot,

344
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:17,480
whenever my brain was still awake

345
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:18,920
and I wasn't too tired,

346
00:20:19,119 --> 00:20:21,240
was how much I wanted to

347
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:22,519
come back to this area,

348
00:20:22,519 --> 00:20:25,640
and explore other paths,

349
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:26,920
just on my own,

350
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:28,440
outside of a race format.

351
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:32,119
We crossed so many different trails,

352
00:20:32,119 --> 00:20:33,440
and there are so many beautiful places,

353
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,720
I'd like to come back to new places,

354
00:20:35,720 --> 00:20:36,920
to keep exploring.

355
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,440
Ten years ago,

356
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:44,880
when I saw others complete the Tor des Géants,

357
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:47,480
I was still a chubby guy weighing about 85 kilos.

358
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:50,720
I lost weight, and then I got into the sport.

359
00:20:51,119 --> 00:20:52,880
If you really like it,

360
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:54,720
and if this film moves you,
